a strikeout. The next pitch, as always happens when crowds do this, is a ball. 2-2. The crowd tries it again, a bit louder this time, and this time Fister gets Drew looking at strike number three. A bit of a squander there, as Red Sox broadcaster Joe Castiglione would say.</p> </div> </div> <div id=\"block-525f2e92e4b0760efba2ae90\" class=\"block\"> <p class=\"block-time published-time\"> <time datetime=\"2013-10-17T01:27:17.929+01:00\">8.27pm <span class=\"timezone\">ET</span></time> </p> <h2 class=\"block-title\">Red Sox 0 - Tigers 0, top of the 2nd</h2> <div class=\"block-elements\"> <p>Jarrod Saltalamacchia, whose one hit in the series was also kinda an important one, pops up the first pitch in foul ground where Cabrera can snag it, leaving Napoli and third with two outs.</p> </div> </div> <div id=\"block-525f2e62e4b0760efba2ae8f\" class=\"block\"> <p class=\"block-time published-time\"> <time datetime=\"2013-10-17T01:25:50.792+01:00\">8.25pm <span class=\"timezone\">ET</span></time> </p> <h2 class=\"block-title\">Red Sox 0 - Tigers 0, top of the 2nd</h2> <div class=\"block-elements\"> <p>Daniel Nava grounds out to Infante, but it moves Napoli over to third base with only one out, so Napoli can score the first run of the game on an out here.</p> </div> </div> <div id=\"block-525f2de4e4b0760efba2ae8d\" class=\"block\"> <p class=\"block-time published-time\"> <time datetime=\"2013-10-17T01:25:03.518+01:00\">8.25pm <span class=\"timezone\">ET</span></time> </p> <h2 class=\"block-title\">Red Sox 0 - Tigers 0, top of the 2nd</h2> <div class=\"block-elements\"> <p>Yesterday's hero Mike Napoli is up and he takes a mighty swing at Fister's first pitch but comes up empty. They can't all be game-winning home runs. Napoli takes the next two pitches for balls before hitting a liner off of Cabrera for what could either be a double or a single with an error depending on how harsh the scorekeeper wants to be to the clearly ailing Cabrera.</p> </div> </div> <div id=\"block-525f2d75e4b0010b6627a8dc\" class=\"block\"> <p class=\"block-time published-time\"> <time datetime=\"2013-10-17T01:22:56.700+01:00\">8.22pm <span class=\"timezone\">ET</span></time> </p> <h2 class=\"block-title\">Red Sox 0 - Tigers 0, top of the 2nd</h2> <div class=\"block-elements\"> <p>Well that was quick. Plus, only one strikeout in an entire inning? This is going to be difficult to adjust.</p> <figure class=\"element element-tweet\" data-canonical-url=\"https://twitter.com/GlobeEricWilbur/statuses/390632677935566848\"> <blockquote class=\"twitter-tweet\"><p>JAKE PEAVY HAS A NO-HITTER!</p>— Eric Wilbur (@GlobeEricWilbur) <a href=\"https://twitter.com/GlobeEricWilbur/statuses/390632677935566848\">October 17, 2013</a></blockquote> </figure> <p>This might be a bit too rash, but I guess technically.</p> </div> </div> <div id=\"block-525f2d4be4b0bbc67cfff3b3\" class=\"block\"> <p class=\"block-time published-time\"> <time datetime=\"2013-10-17T01:21:05.763+01:00\">8.21pm <span class=\"timezone\">ET</span></time> </p> <h2 class=\"block-title\">Red Sox 0 - Tigers 0, bottom of the 1st</h2> <div class=\"block-elements\"> <p>And Prince Fielder grounds out to end the inning faster than I can type &quot;grounds out to end the inning&quot;.</p> </div> </div> <div id=\"block-525f2cc5e4b0bbc67cfff3b2\" class=\"block\"> <p class=\"block-time published-time\"> <time datetime=\"2013-10-17T01:20:23.887+01:00\">8.20pm <span class=\"timezone\">ET</span></time> </p> <h2 class=\"block-title\">Red Sox 0 - Tigers 0, bottom of the 1st</h2> <div class=\"block-elements\"> <p>Jake Peavy gets Miguel Cabrera to strike out, it's not quite as shocking as yesterday's Tazawa stirkeout but it's still a bit curious.</p> </div> </div> <div id=\"block-525f2c35e4b0010b6627a8db\" class=\"block\"> <p class=\"block-time published-time\"> <time datetime=\"2013-10-17T01:18:10.016+01:00\">8.18pm <span class=\"timezone\">ET</span></time> </p> <h2 class=\"block-title\">Red Sox 0 - Tigers 0, bottom of the 1st</h2> <div class=\"block-elements\"> <p>Jake Peavy is on the mound to face not Austin Jackson, but Torii Hunter who may actually hit a baseball with his bat on occasion, if only by accident. Tigers fans will have to hope there<a href=\"http://www.bostonmagazine.com/news/blog/2013/10/16/huntering-like-torii-hunter-new-horganing/#.Ul7H-kV8iVA.twitter\"> will be no Huntering this game</a>. Instead he merely grounds out to Middlebrooks at third.</p> </div> </div> <div id=\"block-525f2b32e4b0bbc67cfff3b0\" class=\"block\"> <p class=\"block-time published-time\"> <time datetime=\"2013-10-17T01:13:52.198+01:00\">8.13pm <span class=\"timezone\">ET</span></time> </p> <h2 class=\"block-title\">Red Sox 0 - Tigers 0, top of the 1st</h2> <div class=\"block-elements\"> <p>David Ortiz, who has only had one hit of the series (but you may remember it from game two), but here he just hits a chopper to second to end the inning. Well, in this series that kinda did count as an offensive explosion.</p> </div> </div> <div id=\"block-525f2afee4b0bbc67cfff3af\" class=\"block\"> <p class=\"block-time published-time\"> <time datetime=\"2013-10-17T01:11:25.498+01:00\">8.11pm <span class=\"timezone\">ET</span></time> </p> <h2 class=\"block-title\">Red Sox 0 - Tigers 0, top of the 1st</h2> <div class=\"block-elements\"> <p>Here's Dustin Pedroia who hits a base hit over Infante, so this time around no four or five innings of no-hit ball from Boston.</p> </div> </div> <div id=\"block-525f2acee4b0bbc67cfff3ae\" class=\"block\"> <p class=\"block-time published-time\"> <time datetime=\"2013-10-17T01:10:32.216+01:00\">8.10pm <span class=\"timezone\">ET</span></time> </p> <h2 class=\"block-title\">Red Sox 0 - Tigers 0, top of the 1st</h2> <div class=\"block-elements\"> <p>Shane Victorino pops up into foul territory for the game's second out.</p> </div> </div> <div id=\"block-525f2a01e4b0010b6627a8da\" class=\"block is-key-event\"> <p class=\"block-time published-time\"> <time datetime=\"2013-10-17T01:09:38.201+01:00\">8.09pm <span class=\"timezone\">ET</span></time> </p> <h2 class=\"block-title\">Red Sox 0 - Tigers 0, top of the 1st</h2> <div class=\"block-elements\"> <p>Fister's first fastball is a strike, that's how you start a postseason game. He's facing Jacoby Ellsbury and quickly gets ahead 0-2. He checks his swing on ball one before grounding out to Infante for the first out of the game.</p> <p>Email from Christopher Henderson:</p> <blockquote class=\"quoted\"> <p>I have a weird feeling that this game will be the rarest of creatures in this year's playoffs, a blowout (something like 8-3). That being said, I have no clue at all as to who the winner will be, but SOMEBODY is due to have a bad day on the mound. Let's say Sox by the aforementioned score, Pedroia doing the major damage.</p> </blockquote> <p>I actually could really see this as well. I mean, these teams are just too good offensively.</p> </div> </div> <div id=\"block-525f29bce4b0bbc67cfff3ad\" class=\"block\"> <p class=\"block-time published-time\"> <time datetime=\"2013-10-17T01:06:14.864+01:00\">8.06pm <span class=\"timezone\">ET</span></time> </p> <h2 class=\"block-title\">Doug Fister</h2> <div class=\"block-elements\"> <p>I will not make a joke involving the fact that Doug Fister was traded for a player named Charlie Furbush. I will not make a joke involving the fact that Doug Fister was traded for a player named Charlie Furbush. I will not make a...</p> </div> </div> <div id=\"block-525f2886e4b0ebb74892f343\" class=\"block\"> <p class=\"block-time published-time\"> <time datetime=\"2013-10-17T01:01:07.233+01:00\">8.01pm <span class=\"timezone\">ET</span></time> </p> <h2 class=\"block-title\">Jose Iglesias</h2> <div class=\"block-elements\"> <p>Why did so many Sox fans fall in love with Jose Iglesias, why did the Tigers want to trade for him? Well he does these sort of things:</p> <figure class=\"element element-video\" data-canonical-url=\"http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=3d2lBWUJnmk\"> <iframe width